Usage

compute_postural_indicators(
  data,
  CoPX_col,
  CoPY_col,
  ID,
  time_col = NULL,
  epoch_length = NULL,
  indicators
)

Arguments

data

a dataframe containing the postural data

CoPX_col

a column in the data frame storing the CoP-X data

CoPY_col

a column in the data frame storing the CoP-Y data

ID

a column in the data frame storing Participants' unique identifiers

time_col

a column in the data frame storing Time course

epoch_length

numeric value: epoch duration over which you want to compute the sway path length (in seconds)

indicators

character string specifying the postural indicator to compute (can take multiple values). Possible values are "CoP_X", "CoP_Y", "SwayPathLength", "EllipseArea", "SD_CoP_X", and/or "SD_CoP_Y".

Value

a data frame containing the new postural measures that was synthetised at the ID level or at the epoch level (if specified).
